Class GoloStruct

  • java.lang.Object
    • gololang.GoloStruct
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<GoloStruct>, java.lang.Iterable<Tuple>

    public abstract class GoloStruct
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<Tuple>, java.lang.Comparable<GoloStruct>
    Base class for Golo structure objects.

    This class defines common behavior. Golo structure classes are final subclasses of this one.

      • __$$_destruct

        public java.lang.Object[] __$$_destruct(int number,
                                        boolean substruct,
                                        java.lang.Object[] toSkip)
        New style destructuring helper.

        The number of variables to be affected must be the number of members. No remainer syntax is allowed.

        Parameters:
        number - number of variable that will be affected.
        substruct - whether the destructuring is complete or should contains a sub structure.
        toSkip - a boolean array indicating the elements to skip.
        Returns:
        an array containing the values to assign.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(GoloStruct other)
        Compares this structure with the specified structure for order.

        Returns a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as this structure is less than, equal to, or greater than the specified structure.

        Two structures are compared by comparing their values(), thus the limitations of Tuple.compareTo(gololang.Tuple) also apply.

        Moreover, two structures are only comparable if they have the same type. For instance, given 

        
 struct StructA = {x, y}
 struct StructB = {a, b}

 let aStructA = StructA(1, 2)
 let aStructB = StructB(1, 3)
        while aStructA: values() < aStructB: values() is valid and true since we compare two 2-tuples, comparing directly the structures aStructA < aStructB throws a ClassCastException.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<GoloStruct>
        Parameters:
        other - the structure to be compared
        Returns:
        a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as this structure is less than, equal to, or greater than the specified structure
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the specified structure is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the structure are of different type, of if the type of the members prevent them from being compared pairwise
        Since:
        Golo3.1
